cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with content caching in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for learning context-specific content popularity, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the regret bound of the proposed algorithm, which is related to theoretical analysis and optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. The paper also mentions service differentiation, which involves system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with caching multimedia content, which is related to multimedia processing and analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
